{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\brdrt}\par\pard
{\f2\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql Originally the purpose of this software was to renew the INVISICLUES(TM) in an electronical way to prevent the final loss of information. In addition there are different places in the internet where you can find more or less complete text versions of the INVISICLUES(TM), but plane text does not match the idea of interactive providing hints. The main purpose of the INIVISICLUES was to provide hints to several parts of a game. These hints were divided into different topics while the hints were sorted due to the level of details provided. The main advantage of these collections in comparision with text-based solutions is that you just get as much help as you need or as you wish. \line \line While developing the system I decided not just to provide a read-only system but also the capabilities to create new  hint collections. By now the new purpose of The Hint Library is to build up a hint file collection. And everyone is invited to take part in this project and develop their favourite hints to other users. (This is not limited to games !).\line To make this software avaible to a wide range of users as many languages as possible shall be supported by the user interface and the online help. I would be very pleased if anyone out there will provide additional language support packs. Please contact me for further information.\line \line Please remember: The sole intent of this software is collecting information, It must not be used for any commercial purposes.\line \line About the software:\line Mainly there are two sections. The first one, ther \i {\uldb Reader}{\v Der_THL_Reader}\i0 , provides capabilites for browsing hintfiles. You will get know explicitly requested information only. Inadvertandly receiving  of information shall be avoided. You will meet the following types of hints: Text, pictures, and  multimedia files( e.g. MIDI, AVI,...)\line For further information please refer to {\uldb Read THL-Files}{\v Der_THL_Reader} section.\line The second part is the \i {\uldb editor}{\v Der_Editor}\i0 , which provides capabilites for creating {\uldb new hint}{\v Das_Hinweis_Editierfenster} collections with an easy to use interface. You can include text, multimedia files ( Sound, Videos ), and pictures ( BMP, JPEG, TARGA, PCX) in your files.\line For further information on {\uldb creating THL files}{\v Eigenentwicklung_von_Hinweissammlungen} please refer to {\uldb The THL Editor}{\v Der_Editor} section.\line The compiler part, which generates a THL file from your raw data is invisible. \line Information about compiling you can find in {\uldb Creating own THL files section}{\v Eigenentwicklung_von_Hinweissammlungen}.\line \line Please send questions, announces or bug reports to:\line Mail:       Stefan Meier, Erfstr. 65, 52249 Eschweiler\line AOL:      SMeier7777\line e-Mail:   SMeier7777@aol.com oder\line                 Stefan.Meier@post.rwth-aachen.de\line \line The Hint Library Homepage:\line ftp://members.aol.com/thlhome\line oder\line http://members.aol.com/thlhome/index.htm\line \line Enjoy THE HINT LIBRARY !\line }\par\pard
{\f0\cf1\li180\ri250\sa-260\fs16\fi0}\par\pard
